ion of objects relative to each other and to fixed locations throughout the scene.\n</p>\n<p>For example, to get the position of a controller relative to the viewer's head, you would compare the controller's <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/XRInputSource/gripSpace\" title=\"gripSpace\"><code>gripSpace</code></a> to the <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/XRReferenceSpace\"><code>XRReferenceSpace</code></a> of type <code>viewer</code>.</p>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"syntax","title":"Syntax","isH3":false,"content":"<div class=\"code-example\"><pre class=\"brush: js-nolint notranslate\">getPose(space, baseSpace)\n</pre></div>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"parameters","title":"Parameters","isH3":true,"content":"<dl>\n  <dt id=\"space\"><code>space</code></dt>\n  <dd>\n    <p>\n      An <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/XRSpace\"><code>XRSpace</code></a> specifying the space for which to obtain an\n      <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/XRPose\"><code>XRPose</code></a> describing the item's position and orientation.\n    </p>\n  </dd>\n  <dt id=\"basespace\"><code>baseSpace</code></dt>\n  <dd>\n    <p>\n      An <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/XRSpace\"><code>XRSpace</code></a> to use as the base or origin for the purposes of computing\n      the relative position and orientation.\n    </p>\n  </dd>\n</dl>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"return_value","title":"Return value","isH3":true,"content":"<p>\n  An <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/XRPose\"><code>XRPose</code></a> object specifying the position and orientation, relative to\n  the <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/XRSpace\"><code>XRSpace</code></a> indicated by <code>baseSpace</code>.\n</p>"}},{"type":"specifications","value":{"title":"Specifications","id":"specifications","isH3":false,"specifications":[{"bcdSpecificationURL":"https://immersive-web.github.io/webxr/#dom-xrframe-getpose","title":"WebXR Device API"}],"query":"api.XRFrame.getPose"}},{"type":"browser_compatibility","value":{"title":"Browser compatibility","id":"bro